<emphasis id="86E0EAA2875DB1071B055A4FFF6BF387" bold="true" box="[92,255,3165,3194]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875DB1071A4C5A4FFCA3F387" authority="Merriam, 1889" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1889" box="[277,823,3165,3194]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="formosus">Perognathus formosus Merriam, 1889</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="04FC3CED875DB10718085A4FFE96F35F" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3802894317" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">St. George, Washington Co., Utah, USA.</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B42B36B0875DB1071CEF570AF596FE4D" blockId="18.[1972,2567,280,708]" pageId="18" pageNumber="211">
Based on detailed sequencing of nDNA and mtDNA genes, C. 
<taxonomicName id="73944D33875DB10712585752F6E1FE9C" authorityName="Merriam" authorityYear="1889" box="[2305,2421,320,353]" class="Mammalia" family="Heteromyidae" genus="Perognathus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="18" pageNumber="211" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="formosus">formosus</taxonomicName>
is one of the three “ancient” clades of coarse-haired pocket mice. Seven subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
